1. Requires a Bachelor’s degree and 12 months or less of relevant professional work experience (excluding internships).
2. U.S. Person (U.S. citizen, permanent resident, or granted refugee or asylee status) as defined here: <https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-22/chapter-I/subchapter-M/part-120/subpart-C/section-120.62>
